Hi everyone, 🖖

I didn't want to create an issue for this topic because I found this report which says that this is an intended behaivour: https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/issues/37749

I couldn't really find something specific in the docs and I was wondering what's a good workaround.

We want to initialize both Tooltips and Popovers using the `selector` option to delegate the click events from body to the desired element. So we don't have to manually re-initialize them after dynamic content changes due to AJAX requests etc.

This causes [this console error](https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/main/js/src/dom/data.js#L26) in data.js because the selector is now indeed the same (`document.body`) for both initializations. This is technically true, however `document.body` is just used to delegate the event and the actual selectors are different. Should this be an exception and not show this error if `selector` is used? In general both Tooltip and Popover work just fine, it just shows the error.

Would you recommend to use some other element as a workaround? For example adding some kind or `.wrapper` element and use this instead for one of the initializations?

Sadly, we don't have a wrapper element at the moment and it seems kind of "strange" to add it to get around this warning. Also, we cannot fiddle around easily with the overall layout because of breaking changes. Omitting delegation and re-initializing manually would cause a lot of extra code. I was wondering if there is a better solution. 🤔 Imo using a different element (e.g. wrapper) would be the "best" workaround, but maybe I'm missing something here.

**[Demo in CodePen](https://codepen.io/tobiasberge/pen/vYaWpZb)** 

EDIT: Just figured our I could also use the `html` element instead of document.body for one initialization. Works fine. But still seems a bit "hacky". 

```js
/**
 * Initializing with selector option shows console error.
 * ---------------------------------------------------- */
new bootstrap.Popover(document.body, {
    selector: '[data-bs-toggle="popover"]',
    trigger: 'focus'
});

// Changing one initialize to another selector e.g. document.querySelector('.container') fixes the issue.
new bootstrap.Tooltip(document.body, {
    selector: '[data-bs-toggle="tooltip"]',
});

/**
 * Normal initialize shows no error.
 * ---------------------------------------------------- */
document.querySelectorAll('[data-bs-toggle="popover"]')
    .forEach(popover => {
        new bootstrap.Popover(popover)
    });

document.querySelectorAll('[data-bs-toggle="tooltip"]')
    .forEach(popover => {
        new bootstrap.Tooltip(popover)
    });
```

