In the [help documentation](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/customize/sass/) for compiling Bootstrap with Sass, the ordering of Bootstrap imports is slightly different than the ordering of the imports in the actual [Bootstrap framework source](https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/v5.3.2/scss/bootstrap.scss).

This is how the imports are structured in the actual framework:

```
// scss-docs-start import-stack
// Configuration
@import "functions";
@import "variables";
@import "variables-dark";
@import "maps";
@import "mixins";
@import "utilities";      // <-- note utilities order

// Layout & components
@import "root";           // <-- note root order
@import "reboot";
@import "type";
// etc.
```

However, in the Sass documentation, the order of imports is different—specifically `root` and `utilities` are reversed throughout the examples on the page:

```
// 1. Include functions first (so you can manipulate colors, SVGs, calc, etc)
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/functions";

// 2. Include any default variable overrides here

// 3. Include remainder of required Bootstrap stylesheets (including any separate color mode stylesheets)
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/variables";
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/variables-dark";

// 4. Include any default map overrides here

// 5. Include remainder of required parts
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/maps";
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/mixins";
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/root";            // <-- note root order

// 6. Optionally include any other parts as needed
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/utilities";       // <-- note utilities order
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/reboot";
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/type";
```

Generally speaking, for compiling Bootstrap from Sass, I'm guessing this is fine and it doesn't matter if `root` and `utilities` are swapped.

However, to keep my Sass compilation time lightning fast in my projects, I like to compile Bootstrap independently of my main site Sass (so that Bootstrap isn't recompiled every time I make a small change to my main site Sass). But I still need access to Bootstrap functions/variables/etc. in my main site Sass, so the question is: **Where should I _stop_ including Bootstrap imports if I just want access to Bootstrap's functions/variables/etc. in my main site Sass, but I don't want any actual Bootstrap CSS rules in my main site CSS?**

Is this the right set of imports?

```
@import "functions";
@import "variables";
@import "variables-dark";
@import "maps";
@import "mixins";
@import "utilities";
```

Or is this the right set of imports?

```
@import "functions";
@import "variables";
@import "variables-dark";
@import "maps";
@import "mixins";
@import "root";
```

Is `root` considered optional, or is `utilities` considered optional, or both or neither?

